text: oh hi everyone anthony fantano here
internet's busiest music nerd and it's
time for a review of the new washed out
album parakosium
washed out is the solo
pop music project of music producer
ernest greene who gained widespread
attention across the music blogosphere
in 2009 via some songs from his life of
leisure ep and not only did the songs on
this ep have a smooth psychedelic sexy
dreamy vibe to them but a lot of music
fans were labeling this aesthetic that
ernest was going for as being a new
genre entirely chill wave and while i
did find the album he followed up that
ep with to be kind of
dull at points i definitely saw the
appeal i think washed out is maybe the
only
chill wave era artist who actually stuck
to his guns but was actually able to
mature the sounds that he was working
with with some more interesting
instrumentation better sound quality and
production i think the only point where
this album really lacked for me was in
the songwriting which had a serious
sameness quality to it throughout the lp
though the grooves on this thing were
great now as far as pericasm goes i
would say that washed out strong points
continue to be strong points and weak
points continue to be
weak points really though i would say on
this album in comparison with washed
out's last full-length lp there is more
attention to melodic detail and
instrumental detail i would say there's
more instrumental diversity on this
thing too in a lot of ways it feels like
washed out as usual and yet there are
spots where it feels like he's pursuing
some different musical ideas but trying
to capture them in this washed-out
aesthetic like on the first full-length
track off of this thing it all feels
right with these upstroked acoustic
guitars it totally has a reggae vibe to
it even the percussion feels subtly
tropical at points i think the only
thing
hiding this influence a little bit is
just how hazy the song is and the very
blatant psychedelic pop influences
especially coming from the string melody
on this thing
the sudden break in momentum that the
song hits after the
verses kind of this slow syrupy chorus
while i don't really care for the sudden
transition i do like the contrast of
these two parts of the song overall it's
a great track to kick this thing off
even if overall the vocals do feel a
little too subdued for me yes i do know
that at this point this is ernest
green's style this is most likely what
he's going to continue delivering on
subsequent albums still
for the length of an entire album it
doesn't convey much of anything to me
other than this sense of listlessness or
bliss there are points where i do feel a
little underwhelmed by the lack of
surprises being presented on this thing
like the track don't give up which is a
nice piece of baleric be if we're going
to look at this thing from a percussive
standpoint and the melody on the chorus
here is pretty nimble too a lot busier
than what you'll usually hear from
washed out but in terms of the verses
the groove the vocal melody it all feels
eerily similar to something he had done
on his previous album however the track
weightless to me is is one of my
favorites on here because what's
happening here to me feels like kind of
a rarity from washed out it is an
honest-to-god ballad with the vocal
melody really leading the way on this
thing as opposed to the beat the very
slow spacious drum machines and synth
arpeggios on this track had me feeling
like i was listening to this syrupy
piece of of new wave i know washed out
has always had a very prevalent 80s
music influence going on in his tracks
but this is the first time where i feel
like i'm hearing a sincere
recreation going on here is as well as
the song fall back with these very tight
16th note high hats just a very busy
beat on this song and this vocal
phrasing that really reminds me of
bernard sumner there are tracks on here
that i really enjoy highlights just like
the previous few washed out releases but
again there are tracks here that i just
feel like do nothing for me or have this
real kind of hollowness to them tracks
that i just wish had a bit more body to
them a bit more detail the song all i
know for example for all intents and
purposes to me sounds like the
soundtrack to a car commercial nearly
every sound in this song has has no
personality to it if it wasn't for the
hazy effects and the vocals i would have
never guessed this track was from washed
out the very gentle piano arpeggios and
and the basic root note bass lines
playing out this a e d chord progression
it's boring
i feel like the tracks one chance to
redeem itself came around the solo or
the interlude that was placed in there
which has i'm not sure i can't tell if
it's a horn or it's a string or it's
just some midi instrument either way it
just plays a handful of do nothing notes
that really have
nothing behind them it's like they were
randomized i think the closing track on
on this lp has a similarly basic vibe to
it too that keeps
what what could have been a pretty good
song from being an interestingly
detailed or layered beautiful piece of
music again and again and again washed
out misses out on making some good
tracks because the effects kind of take
hold and the music really sits on the
back burner again ernest green excels
when it comes to creating vibes
moods and dishing out grooves if those
are your primary focuses if those are
your primary interest in music then
forget what i say and
get this record because there's
definitely some better production and a
better sound set and an interesting
array of influences going on with this
lp from psychedelic pop to caribbean
music and dream pop as well as synth pop
and new wave however on the musical side
of things there's just not enough
diversity on this lp
really and these very subtle changes in
influence and instrumentation just
aren't enough to keep this album from
feeling a little monotonous i'm really
kind of feeling a strong six on on this
thing if you've given it a listen what
did you think of it did you love it hate
it why what do you think i should review
next and
that's it this review is my opinion if
you don't like it here's a straw i want
to give a shout out to flying lotus and
eclectic only the strong subscribe all
mistakes were intentional anthony
fantano washed out forever
